00:57:27,370 --> 00:57:31,770
And then you can answer that
question on that very pure level.

716
00:57:32,610 --> 00:57:36,810
Those are preliminary questions,
then we move on to the real ones.

717
00:57:36,970 --> 00:57:40,410
What do you desire
for the coming generation?

718
00:57:40,570 --> 00:57:44,210
What do you wish to pass on to
your kids? What'd be your legacy?

719
00:57:44,370 --> 00:57:49,370
We've already moved a step from a
focus on "me" to a focus on society.

720
00:57:49,890 --> 00:57:53,130
And then if we then
take a third step and ask,

721
00:57:53,690 --> 00:57:57,050
"And what do you think?
How will society actually be?"

722
00:57:57,250 --> 00:58:00,250
Those steps get us
something utterly different

723
00:58:00,410 --> 00:58:03,330
than going right to
that third level does.

724
00:58:03,490 --> 00:58:07,970
You're absolutely right, then people
stay in their own little lives.

725
00:58:10,850 --> 00:58:15,730
If you were given carte blanche what
would you change in our society?

726
00:58:15,890 --> 00:58:20,450
What we see is that income is important
and, of course, so is education.

727
00:58:20,610 --> 00:58:22,970
There's no doubt about that.

728
00:58:23,130 --> 00:58:26,570
But when we consider
which people have visions,

729
00:58:26,730 --> 00:58:31,450
which people see life as an opportunity
to shape the things around them

730
00:58:31,930 --> 00:58:34,130
and see life as worth shaping.

731
00:58:34,330 --> 00:58:38,090
Increasingly those are people
with true circles of friends.

732
00:58:38,290 --> 00:58:41,690
And not lots of friends
who are all from the same place,

733
00:58:41,850 --> 00:58:44,250
as was once perhaps
the case for me,

734
00:58:44,410 --> 00:58:50,250
but friends from different countries
and from a diverse array of backgrounds.

735
00:58:50,410 --> 00:58:53,570
People of varying ages
and sexual orientations.

736
00:58:53,970 --> 00:58:56,210
And that can be facilitated.

737
00:58:56,370 --> 00:58:59,770
That's something I think
society does less and less.

738
00:59:00,570 --> 00:59:06,370
We've noticed that those various groups
are increasingly staying among themselves.

739
00:59:06,530 --> 00:59:11,610
And so what I would recommend
is a mandatory social year.

740
00:59:11,770 --> 00:59:14,890
That there's a kind of
mandatory exchange

741
00:59:15,050 --> 00:59:17,450
with people in other countries.

742
00:59:17,610 --> 00:59:21,250
We have to introduce people,
young people, to that

743
00:59:21,410 --> 00:59:25,930
so that we don't stay in one little
spot in Germany our entire lives.

744
00:59:26,490 --> 00:59:30,410
So we want to open up and have
to open up to the wider world.

745
00:59:30,970 --> 00:59:34,090
You can't force that on people,
they have to want it.

746
00:59:34,290 --> 00:59:39,530
And the will to do that comes with
one-to-one contact, with experience.

747
00:59:39,690 --> 00:59:41,850
People with a broader focus?

748
00:59:42,010 --> 00:59:46,130
Pessimistic people say, "The
feeling of togetherness is lovely,

749
00:59:46,330 --> 00:59:48,330
